It  is a very  powerful chemical poison.<br>
2. There are two types of plutonium 239.<br>
These are alpha phase plutonium which contains<br>
large amounts of pu240 which undergoes spontaneous fission<br>
thus releasing deadly neutron radiation, and delta phase<br>
plutonium which has no Pu-240. Delta phase plutonium does<br>
not undergo spontaneous fission. Delta phase plutonium<br>
is an alpha particle emitter only which undergoes<br>
the alpha radioactive decay proccess to change into lead .<br>
3.  Exposure to alpha phase plutonium can inflict a lethal<br>
radiation dose on you given sufficient time.<br>
4.Exposure to delta phase plutonium is harmless to you so long as you do not get it inside your body, and the  amount of it you are exposed  to  is less then a critical mass.<br>
Your skin will stop the alpha particles from penetrating more<br>
then skin deep into you body. Prolonged exposure of<br>
your skin to alpha particles can cause skin cancer however.<br>
If you get an alpha particle emitter inside your body for a long time period  it can cause cancer that way however.<br>
<br>
